<br>
Thus, the decision to give mages post-50 pet heals was obviously a pure balance decision, and not in tone with the natural order of the two classes.  I wanted to mention this because I sense that for some reason people here think that the current balance is &quot;sacred&quot; and that whatever is currently true MUST be true post-expansion.  This is a false assumption - when mages received pet-heals none were given to necromancers, despite the fact that necros had them in the past.  Similarly, (to give a more recent example) necros receive a level 60 ancient nuke that is nearly as good as mages (including mage ancient), despite the fact that mages have always been vastly superior to necros at nuking in the past.  Similarly, mages were simply atrocious at regenning mana until recently, with mod rod II and AA's, with which mages can surpass even necros at mana regen.  <br>
<br>
